1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:08,170
♪

2
00:00:08,170 --> 00:00:12,140
(singing in foreign language)

3
00:00:12,140 --> 00:01:45,180
♪

4
00:01:50,070 --> 00:01:53,080
(birdsong)

5
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:02,010
It's wonderful
to be back home.

6
00:02:02,010 --> 00:02:03,070
Smell the air.

7
00:02:03,070 --> 00:02:08,210
♪

8
00:02:08,210 --> 00:02:11,290
And pretty soon,
it'll be white again.

9
00:02:11,290 --> 00:02:14,020
Nothing's changed here.

10
00:02:14,020 --> 00:02:15,030
Everything's the same.

11
00:02:15,030 --> 00:02:16,090
Unbelievable.

12
00:02:16,090 --> 00:02:18,070
It's hard to believe
that our very own Kenshin

13
00:02:18,070 --> 00:02:19,130
just won a battle in which

14
00:02:19,130 --> 00:02:22,120
our country's fate
hung in the balance.

15
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:23,220
Mm-hmm.

16
00:02:23,220 --> 00:02:25,070
Now let's see how it looks.

17
00:02:25,070 --> 00:02:26,220
-Wow!
-It looks better.

18
00:02:26,220 --> 00:02:28,080
-You're a good scrubber.
-Great, just two more

19
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:29,190
and we'll be all done.

20
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:30,180
So I got to admit,

21
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:32,030
all this work is
making me hungry.

22
00:02:32,030 --> 00:02:33,210
So what's for lunch,
lobster, red snapper,

23
00:02:33,210 --> 00:02:36,140
hey, I don't mind if all
you got is pickled eel.

24
00:02:36,140 --> 00:02:37,180
-Heh!
-Ugh!

25
00:02:37,180 --> 00:02:38,170
Shame on you.

26
00:02:38,170 --> 00:02:40,070
You're the laziest
bum I've ever seen

27
00:02:40,070 --> 00:02:41,220
and the fact that you
think you're entitled

28
00:02:41,220 --> 00:02:44,130
to anything more than a kick
in the butt is unbelievable.

29
00:02:44,130 --> 00:02:45,260
You need to go on
another long trip

30
00:02:45,260 --> 00:02:48,030
and pound some rocks
with your fists again.

31
00:02:48,030 --> 00:02:50,080
Maybe you're the one
that needs a little pounding!

32
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,160
As a fighter,
you're so lame

33
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:53,150
you couldn't beat
an egg with a fork.

34
00:02:53,150 --> 00:02:54,270
You've gone too far!

35
00:02:54,270 --> 00:02:56,050
-Hey!
-And I've had it!

36
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:57,100
Stop it right now!

37
00:02:57,100 --> 00:02:59,110
If you two ever want to
get any food from me again,

38
00:02:59,110 --> 00:03:00,220
you'd better follow me.

39
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:03,080
Sano, it's been almost a year

40
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:05,000
since you put
this hole in the wall.

41
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,140
And since you're responsible
for creating this eyesore,

42
00:03:07,140 --> 00:03:10,010
I'm sure you can understand
why I want you to fix it.

43
00:03:10,010 --> 00:03:12,110
Hey now, it wasn't me
who made that hole, Kori,

44
00:03:12,110 --> 00:03:14,130
that was Saito's
doing, I tell ya.

45
00:03:14,130 --> 00:03:16,030
You will fix it, now!

46
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:19,010
Ooh, ouch-a, she got ya.

47
00:03:19,010 --> 00:03:21,150
And Yoshi, you need to
earn your keep as well.

48
00:03:21,150 --> 00:03:23,100
That hole let
a lot of dirt in here

49
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:24,250
and I need you
to clean it up.

50
00:03:24,250 --> 00:03:27,290
I want you to mop and scrub
the floor ten times today.

51
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:30,060
Ten times, but I--

52
00:03:30,060 --> 00:03:32,220
Miss Kori, I finished the
laundry and watering the garden,

53
00:03:32,220 --> 00:03:34,000
is there anything else?

54
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,060
Thanks, follow me, Kenshin.

55
00:03:36,060 --> 00:03:39,060
(papers rustling)

56
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:41,090
There's something in here
that can help all of us.

57
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,000
There you go.

58
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,010
This is a very
thin bamboo sword.

59
00:03:47,010 --> 00:03:48,240
It's for fishing.

60
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,170
Fishing?

61
00:03:49,170 --> 00:03:50,200
It's a fishing pole.

62
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:52,190
You see, we spent all our
money trying to find you,

63
00:03:52,190 --> 00:03:54,080
so we have no food money.

64
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:55,250
So I was hoping
you'd take that pole

65
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:58,160
and go fishing so we might
have something for dinner.

66
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:02,140
(grumbling)

67
00:04:02,140 --> 00:04:05,210
Hey, Kenshin, get out there
and catch us a bunch of fish.

68
00:04:05,210 --> 00:04:07,250
Go for it, we'll be working,

69
00:04:07,250 --> 00:04:11,100
so by the time you get back
here, we'll be starving!

70
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:14,280
And you know how cranky
I get when I don't eat!

71
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:16,110
-Wish us luck.
-Bye-bye.

72
00:04:16,110 --> 00:04:18,010
Hope you catch some fish.

73
00:04:21,170 --> 00:04:23,270
Now we should get started.

74
00:04:23,270 --> 00:04:25,030
Oh!

75
00:04:25,030 --> 00:04:27,200
♪

76
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:29,020
June 22nd.

77
00:04:29,020 --> 00:04:31,150
The calendar on the wall
shows that time stopped here

78
00:04:31,150 --> 00:04:33,010
almost a year ago.

79
00:04:33,010 --> 00:04:34,180
I'll never be able
to forget the day

80
00:04:34,180 --> 00:04:36,190
that the whole
world stopped for me.

81
00:04:36,190 --> 00:04:40,270
♪

82
00:04:40,270 --> 00:04:43,040
I remember what he said
when he was leaving,

83
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:46,180
and how it made me feel.

84
00:04:46,180 --> 00:04:49,200
I'll never forget that
warm early summer night.

85
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,080
It was the first
day in my life

86
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:53,050
that I felt like a woman.

87
00:04:53,050 --> 00:04:55,260
♪

88
00:04:55,260 --> 00:04:59,210
(stream babbling)

89
00:04:59,210 --> 00:05:01,160
This looks like a good spot.

90
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:04,030
Hmm, uh, uh.

91
00:05:05,140 --> 00:05:06,280
That'll work.

92
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:09,260
(water babbling)

93
00:05:09,260 --> 00:05:12,120
(birdsong)

94
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:15,030
(water babbling)

95
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:21,030
Kenshin, when are
you gonna catch a whale?

96
00:05:21,030 --> 00:05:22,030
A fish would do.

97
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:23,260
You know, I think
I got a bite.

98
00:05:23,260 --> 00:05:25,090
-Huh!
-Huh!

99
00:05:25,090 --> 00:05:27,190
Oh.

100
00:05:27,190 --> 00:05:29,290
Look, it's our
fisherman friend.

101
00:05:29,290 --> 00:05:32,150
He always catches
a lot of fish.

102
00:05:36,070 --> 00:05:38,040
Mister, will you
teach us how to fish?

103
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:40,030
We're coming to see you.

104
00:05:40,030 --> 00:05:42,080
♪

105
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,290
Hey, kid, you didn't
ask for permission

106
00:05:43,290 --> 00:05:45,180
to cross our bridge.

107
00:05:45,180 --> 00:05:48,240
Yeah, that's gonna
cost you some money.

108
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:51,160
We know your dad's rich
so you better hand it over.

109
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:54,160
Please, somebody,
anybody, help me.

110
00:05:57,130 --> 00:05:58,150
Huh?

111
00:05:58,150 --> 00:06:00,120
(menacing laughter)

112
00:06:02,150 --> 00:06:05,090
Well, we did warn you, kid.

113
00:06:06,210 --> 00:06:09,160
(groaning)

114
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,220
What the hell
happened to him?

115
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:11,250
Maybe bad sushi.

116
00:06:11,250 --> 00:06:13,110
Hey, where's my dagger?

117
00:06:13,110 --> 00:06:15,000
It just vanished
into thin air.

118
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,180
(groaning)

119
00:06:16,180 --> 00:06:18,220
♪

120
00:06:18,220 --> 00:06:20,130
Who is this guy?

121
00:06:20,130 --> 00:06:24,150
♪

122
00:06:24,150 --> 00:06:26,250
What an exhibition
of precision and speed.

123
00:06:26,250 --> 00:06:28,200
He moves with
the power of a master,

124
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:30,190
the stealth of a ninja.

125
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:31,260
Who is he?

126
00:06:31,260 --> 00:06:33,240
(metal whizzing)

127
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,220
(splash)

128
00:06:34,220 --> 00:06:35,210
If I didn't know better,

129
00:06:35,210 --> 00:06:36,220
I'd say there's
a spirit around here.

130
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:38,110
It must be a ghost
of the river.

131
00:06:38,110 --> 00:06:41,120
You thugs get away
from my son!

132
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:44,030
So you like
bullying my son, huh?

133
00:06:44,030 --> 00:06:45,180
Well, it's your turn.

134
00:06:45,180 --> 00:06:46,150
Take this.

135
00:06:46,150 --> 00:06:48,090
(punch)

136
00:06:48,090 --> 00:06:50,070
(water gurgling)

137
00:06:50,070 --> 00:06:51,270
I bet you won't
be trying that again.

138
00:06:51,270 --> 00:06:52,270
Yeah, jerk.

139
00:06:52,270 --> 00:06:55,270
(footsteps)

140
00:06:55,270 --> 00:06:59,110
(gasping)

141
00:06:59,110 --> 00:07:02,200
They pushed down our friend,
and now he's dead!

142
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:04,200
Let your grief
fly away, children.

143
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:07,150
-Huh?
-Wow!

144
00:07:07,150 --> 00:07:09,100
I promised you
these last time.

145
00:07:09,100 --> 00:07:11,290
Wow, thank you, mister.

146
00:07:11,290 --> 00:07:13,220
You could have sat
at that spot for ten years

147
00:07:13,220 --> 00:07:15,150
and not caught a fish.

148
00:07:15,150 --> 00:07:18,150
(water babbling)

149
00:07:18,150 --> 00:07:19,170
I can help.

150
00:07:19,170 --> 00:07:22,190
I know a much
better fishing spot.

151
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:27,100
♪

152
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:29,150
-There.
-Oh.

153
00:07:29,150 --> 00:07:31,010
(giggling)

154
00:07:31,010 --> 00:07:41,010
♪

155
00:07:41,010 --> 00:07:43,140
We've been given
a perfect day for fishing.

156
00:07:43,140 --> 00:07:46,290
♪

157
00:07:46,290 --> 00:07:49,150
I feel like you have
so much good in your heart.

158
00:07:49,150 --> 00:07:50,280
I know it's not my business,

159
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:53,130
but when did you quit
being a slasher?

160
00:07:53,130 --> 00:07:54,250
You know, I've
met quite a few

161
00:07:54,250 --> 00:07:56,150
of the new
generation of slashers,

162
00:07:56,150 --> 00:07:58,240
but none of them
were as humble and kind

163
00:07:58,240 --> 00:08:01,170
as I get the feeling you are.

164
00:08:01,170 --> 00:08:03,240
I watched how you dealt with
those thugs on the bridge.

165
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:05,230
You used your
skills so subtly.

166
00:08:05,230 --> 00:08:09,210
Here we sit, two swordsmen
who've lost their fangs.

167
00:08:09,210 --> 00:08:11,040
Fate has been
good to both of us.

168
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:12,260
It's allowed us
to live long enough

169
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:15,100
to have this
opportunity to meet.

170
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:18,000
I feel like you have
a story I should hear.

171
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,050
Hmm.

172
00:08:20,050 --> 00:08:22,170
Have you ever been here
in the summer at night?

173
00:08:22,170 --> 00:08:25,140
This whole place
is filled with fireflies.

174
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:27,060
That's why this place
used to be called

175
00:08:27,060 --> 00:08:29,180
Wishing Firefly Bend.

176
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:31,110
Wishing Firefly?

177
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:35,100
Yes, that's what they
called it a long time ago.

178
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:37,140
What I'm about to tell
you happened many years

179
00:08:37,140 --> 00:08:39,200
before the Edo era had ended.

180
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:42,120
It's a story that will
certainly interest you.

181
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:44,180
And it's my story to tell.

182
00:08:46,030 --> 00:08:48,020
Match!

183
00:08:48,020 --> 00:08:49,200
I've never seen
such technique.

184
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:52,090
Yeah, he's got all that
talent and he's only 16.

185
00:08:56,110 --> 00:08:59,220
Hey, Ryunosuke,
congratulations!

186
00:08:59,220 --> 00:09:01,200
It was amazing
the way you won that match.

187
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:03,130
That guy had a lot more
experience than you,

188
00:09:03,130 --> 00:09:04,170
but you still won.

189
00:09:04,170 --> 00:09:06,040
I don't think there's
a swordsman in all of Edo

190
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:08,020
that's better than you.

191
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:09,210
I heard this rumor--
I was wondering,

192
00:09:09,210 --> 00:09:11,210
were you really asked
to do a demonstration

193
00:09:11,210 --> 00:09:13,020
in front of the Shogun?

194
00:09:13,020 --> 00:09:14,290
Yes, and I declined.

195
00:09:14,290 --> 00:09:15,260
It's silly.

196
00:09:15,260 --> 00:09:16,260
You did what?

197
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:17,240
Are you crazy?

198
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:19,100
Why'd you do that?

199
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,180
I'm just not
really satisfied

200
00:09:20,180 --> 00:09:22,130
with my sword fighting
skills yet.

201
00:09:22,130 --> 00:09:24,030
I can't tell how
good a fighter I am

202
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:25,290
from these sparring matches.

203
00:09:25,290 --> 00:09:27,110
There's really only
one way to find out

204
00:09:27,110 --> 00:09:29,040
if I'm as good
as you say I am.

205
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:31,020
And it's not
with a bamboo sword.

206
00:09:31,020 --> 00:09:32,040
I want to get better,

207
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:33,100
and the only way
to achieve that

208
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:34,210
is the way of the Samurai.

209
00:09:34,210 --> 00:09:36,130
To truly put yourself
in harms way.

210
00:09:36,130 --> 00:09:38,270
You attain real strength
only by experiencing danger.

211
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:41,140
But you are strong,
I don't understand.

212
00:09:41,140 --> 00:09:43,060
Well, you can never
be too strong.

213
00:09:43,060 --> 00:09:46,070
I just want to achieve
absolute strength.

214
00:09:46,070 --> 00:09:54,060
♪

215
00:09:54,060 --> 00:09:55,040
Do you know that
girl over there?

216
00:09:55,040 --> 00:09:56,090
That's my sister Kinu,

217
00:09:56,090 --> 00:09:58,150
I've introduced
you to her five times.

218
00:09:58,150 --> 00:09:59,260
Kinu, say hi.

219
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:02,200
Ah, come on,
don't get shy now.

220
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:04,070
Hey, where are you going?

221
00:10:04,070 --> 00:10:06,170
♪

222
00:10:06,170 --> 00:10:07,170
For a guy that's so sharp,

223
00:10:07,170 --> 00:10:09,170
you sure don't see
what's around you.

224
00:10:09,170 --> 00:10:11,250
What?

225
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:15,040
You ever heard of
Wishing Firefly Bend?

226
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:17,090
It's this place on the river,
that legend has it,

227
00:10:17,090 --> 00:10:19,110
if you go there and pray
every day for a year

228
00:10:19,110 --> 00:10:20,190
for something to happen,

229
00:10:20,190 --> 00:10:22,140
the fireflies
make your wish come true

230
00:10:22,140 --> 00:10:24,120
when they arrive
in early summer.

231
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,110
Firefly Bend?

232
00:10:25,110 --> 00:10:26,110
That's the place.

233
00:10:26,110 --> 00:10:28,040
My sister has been
going there for two months

234
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:29,150
to try and get the fireflies

235
00:10:29,150 --> 00:10:31,230
to let you know how
she feels about you.

236
00:10:31,230 --> 00:10:33,220
Kinu's pretty shy
when it comes to guys.

237
00:10:33,220 --> 00:10:36,190
But I guess she must
like you a whole lot.

238
00:10:36,190 --> 00:10:38,010
Huh?

239
00:10:38,010 --> 00:10:39,000
Not long after that,

240
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,160
fate decided that
my world should change.

241
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:44,220
From sunny days
to the cold, dark night,

242
00:10:44,220 --> 00:10:46,150
the fates had heard me.

243
00:10:46,150 --> 00:10:48,260
I never had to pray
to the fireflies.

244
00:10:48,260 --> 00:10:50,210
But as a wise
philosopher said,

245
00:10:50,210 --> 00:10:52,280
"Be careful
what you wish for."

246
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:55,090
My life changed that
dark, stormy night,

247
00:10:55,090 --> 00:10:57,200
and it was just a matter
of being somewhere

248
00:10:57,200 --> 00:11:00,040
when something happened.

249
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:05,040
(thunder cracking)

250
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,170
Get him, stop him!

251
00:11:06,170 --> 00:11:08,010
He just robbed us!

252
00:11:08,010 --> 00:11:11,090
♪

253
00:11:11,090 --> 00:11:13,180
So you think you can get away
with dishonoring our house

254
00:11:13,180 --> 00:11:15,280
by taking what
is rightfully ours?

255
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:18,050
You must die for your crime!

256
00:11:18,050 --> 00:11:23,170
♪

257
00:11:23,170 --> 00:11:24,220
Arrgh!

258
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:26,110
Ugh!

259
00:11:26,110 --> 00:11:47,230
♪

260
00:11:47,230 --> 00:11:50,210
(whinnying)

261
00:11:50,210 --> 00:11:52,240
This ninja wasn't
just some petty thief,

262
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:55,130
he was truly a ninja
who meted out death

263
00:11:55,130 --> 00:11:57,230
with the sword of thunder god.

264
00:11:57,230 --> 00:12:01,000
I was amazed at what I saw
in the faces of the dead men.

265
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:04,090
All of them had restful
expressions on their faces.

266
00:12:04,090 --> 00:12:06,050
It was obvious
they had died so quickly

267
00:12:06,050 --> 00:12:07,250
that they never
knew what hit them.

268
00:12:07,250 --> 00:12:09,100
And it scared me.

269
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:11,020
There's one still alive!

270
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:17,130
♪

271
00:12:17,130 --> 00:12:19,230
Argh!

272
00:12:19,230 --> 00:12:26,000
♪

273
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,240
(sword slashing)

274
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:33,230
♪

275
00:12:33,230 --> 00:12:37,020
That night was the first
time I killed a man.

276
00:12:37,020 --> 00:12:43,110
♪

277
00:12:48,110 --> 00:12:51,050
I had to explain
a difficult decision.

278
00:12:53,130 --> 00:12:54,220
That's not possible.

279
00:12:54,220 --> 00:12:56,270
You would never do
anything like that.

280
00:12:56,270 --> 00:12:58,130
I know you,
I know your heart,

281
00:12:58,130 --> 00:12:59,240
and you are not a killer.

282
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:01,140
But I could develop
a taste for blood.

283
00:13:01,140 --> 00:13:03,130
If I'm ever going
to be a great swordsman,

284
00:13:03,130 --> 00:13:05,060
death is certainly
part of the journey.

285
00:13:05,060 --> 00:13:06,170
It's kill or be killed.

286
00:13:06,170 --> 00:13:08,030
You stop this talk.

287
00:13:08,030 --> 00:13:09,250
Listen, I care about
what happens to you,

288
00:13:09,250 --> 00:13:10,190
so don't go!

289
00:13:10,190 --> 00:13:11,160
Enough.

290
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:13,230
Ryunosuke, I beg of you, stay.

291
00:13:13,230 --> 00:13:15,000
If you're really
going to kill again,

292
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,010
then I ask you
to please kill me first.

293
00:13:17,010 --> 00:13:21,240
♪

294
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:24,030
(sobbing)

295
00:13:24,030 --> 00:13:28,260
♪

296
00:13:28,260 --> 00:13:31,100
You could never
understand my dreams!

297
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:33,220
No!

298
00:13:33,220 --> 00:13:35,090
Don't leave me!

299
00:13:35,090 --> 00:13:39,090
♪

300
00:13:39,090 --> 00:13:41,270
I left that day and
tried to forget Kinu.

301
00:13:41,270 --> 00:13:45,000
I went on a rampage to
prove myself as a swordsman.

302
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:45,389
Soon after that,

303
00:13:45,389 --> 00:13:49,200
death became a very
close associate of mine.

304
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,050
No matter how much I killed,

305
00:13:51,050 --> 00:13:53,240
I never felt
satisfied with myself.

306
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:56,270
My heart was filled
with discontent.

307
00:13:58,050 --> 00:14:01,220
The years dragged on and
I had no friends, no life,

308
00:14:01,220 --> 00:14:04,260
and what I had chosen
for a life began to haunt me.

309
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:24,080
♪

310
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:26,260
I was no longer
living life,

311
00:14:26,260 --> 00:14:29,170
I merely existed.

312
00:14:29,170 --> 00:14:31,290
I was chasing
an impossible dream.

313
00:14:31,290 --> 00:14:32,260
I didn't know it,

314
00:14:32,260 --> 00:14:35,000
but I was trying to
relive that stormy night

315
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:38,000
when I'd been forced
to tap my savage power.

316
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:47,210
♪

317
00:14:47,210 --> 00:14:50,230
No, this isn't it,
I haven't found it.

318
00:14:50,230 --> 00:14:55,040
I was the heartless, faceless,
nameless messenger of death.

319
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:59,070
One day, 15 years
had passed me by.

320
00:14:59,070 --> 00:15:01,190
Finally, after
21 years of wandering,

321
00:15:01,190 --> 00:15:06,220
fate imposed itself once again
into my desolate existence.

322
00:15:06,220 --> 00:15:08,230
Help, stop that thief!

323
00:15:08,230 --> 00:15:10,200
He killed our son!

324
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:14,140
(horse galloping)

325
00:15:14,140 --> 00:15:15,140
It's him!

326
00:15:16,230 --> 00:15:19,160
Even after all that time,
I knew it was him!

327
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:21,120
The ninja that had
changed my life!

328
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:26,280
♪

329
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:30,030
I felt the same rage
that I had felt so long ago.

330
00:15:30,030 --> 00:15:56,100
♪

331
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:58,010
(swords clanking)

332
00:15:58,010 --> 00:16:15,290
♪

333
00:16:15,290 --> 00:16:18,090
When I saw him lying
there dead, I shuddered.

334
00:16:18,090 --> 00:16:20,180
His face was etched
with the same serene look

335
00:16:20,180 --> 00:16:22,170
of those men he had
killed on that rainy night

336
00:16:22,170 --> 00:16:25,110
over 20 years ago.

337
00:16:25,110 --> 00:16:26,140
And it was then I realized

338
00:16:26,140 --> 00:16:29,140
there was no longer
a reason for me to kill.

339
00:16:29,140 --> 00:16:31,030
I had finally
survived long enough

340
00:16:31,030 --> 00:16:33,100
to achieve my sick dream.

341
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:36,030
I had become a monster,
just like him.

342
00:16:36,030 --> 00:16:39,190
♪

343
00:16:39,190 --> 00:16:44,110
(sobbing)

344
00:16:44,110 --> 00:16:55,200
♪

345
00:16:59,190 --> 00:17:01,100
I woke up to a nightmare.

346
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:02,190
I was left with nothing

347
00:17:02,190 --> 00:17:04,180
but guilt for
the youth I'd wasted

348
00:17:04,180 --> 00:17:06,150
and the lives I'd taken.

349
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:08,040
(gasping)

350
00:17:08,040 --> 00:17:09,210
Ah!

351
00:17:09,210 --> 00:17:18,260
♪

352
00:17:18,260 --> 00:17:22,220
N-n-n-no!

353
00:17:22,220 --> 00:17:24,060
I can't take it!

354
00:17:24,060 --> 00:17:26,150
How could I have thought
of life as so worthless?

355
00:17:26,150 --> 00:17:28,270
I was so wrong!

356
00:17:28,270 --> 00:17:30,070
Tell me why!

357
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:32,280
How could I?

358
00:17:32,280 --> 00:17:34,280
Why did I give up
my life for this hell?

359
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:37,200
(gasping)

360
00:17:41,260 --> 00:17:44,220
(crickets chirping)

361
00:17:53,270 --> 00:17:55,280
Ryunosuke.

362
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:57,070
Ryunosuke.

363
00:17:57,070 --> 00:17:59,180
(water rushing)

364
00:18:01,130 --> 00:18:15,270
♪

365
00:18:15,270 --> 00:18:17,280
It's finally over.

366
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:20,070
Your long journey
to find your soul

367
00:18:20,070 --> 00:18:22,260
has finally been completed.

368
00:18:22,260 --> 00:18:25,260
I have waited such
a long time to hold you.

369
00:18:25,260 --> 00:18:34,000
♪

370
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:37,090
I've been waiting
all these years.

371
00:18:37,090 --> 00:19:10,110
♪

372
00:19:10,110 --> 00:19:14,170
I knew I must return to home,
where my life had meaning

373
00:19:14,170 --> 00:19:17,200
and there was someone
who loved me.

374
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:19,070
Greetings, I bet
you've come here

375
00:19:19,070 --> 00:19:22,080
because you've heard about
Wishing Firefly Bend, right?

376
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:24,030
Hey, you're Shinpachi.

377
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:26,260
That's me, but, uh,
I don't recognize you.

378
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:29,080
Uh, you must have known
my sister Kinu.

379
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:30,080
She waited her whole life

380
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:32,140
for a man who left
and never returned.

381
00:19:32,140 --> 00:19:33,110
I really miss her.

382
00:19:33,110 --> 00:19:35,060
She died seven
years ago today.

383
00:19:35,060 --> 00:19:38,130
♪

384
00:19:38,130 --> 00:19:39,180
But she had a great spirit.

385
00:19:39,180 --> 00:19:40,270
She never stopped believing.

386
00:19:40,270 --> 00:19:43,050
(gasps)

387
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:56,120
♪

388
00:19:56,120 --> 00:19:59,040
I'm so glad you
finally came home.

389
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:01,190
Now we will be
together forever.

390
00:20:01,190 --> 00:20:03,140
Even though I have
left this Earth,

391
00:20:03,140 --> 00:20:05,240
our souls will never part.

392
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:12,000
♪

393
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:14,010
(water rushing)

394
00:20:17,110 --> 00:20:18,120
So there you have it.

395
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:19,270
That's my story.

396
00:20:19,270 --> 00:20:23,090
And it's not a fable,
it happened to me right here.

397
00:20:23,090 --> 00:20:24,220
Wishing Firefly.

398
00:20:24,220 --> 00:20:26,280
(water gurgling)

399
00:20:30,210 --> 00:20:34,070
Somehow I feel like your
story is very familiar.

400
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:41,200
Anyway, it's late,
time for me to leave.

401
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:44,150
Wait, are you really
going home already, mister?

402
00:20:44,150 --> 00:20:46,010
You be good until
I see you again.

403
00:20:46,010 --> 00:20:46,356
Oh, I'll be good,

404
00:20:46,356 --> 00:20:49,040
I just want to hear
more stories next time.

405
00:20:49,040 --> 00:20:51,220
Uh, excuse me,
there's just one thing.

406
00:20:51,220 --> 00:20:54,210
There is one important
question I want to ask you.

407
00:20:54,210 --> 00:20:57,000
When a man loves a woman
and he ignores that love

408
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,050
to follow his goals--

409
00:20:58,050 --> 00:21:01,270
I guess what I'm asking is,
do you regret it?

410
00:21:01,270 --> 00:21:04,020
A wise question.

411
00:21:04,020 --> 00:21:05,140
I have many regrets.

412
00:21:05,140 --> 00:21:07,210
Certainly, I regret
wasting most of my life

413
00:21:07,210 --> 00:21:11,050
searching for something to let
me know I was good enough.

414
00:21:11,050 --> 00:21:13,120
But I think my biggest
regret is that I left behind

415
00:21:13,120 --> 00:21:15,040
the true love of my life.

416
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,270
I never got to
experience the love

417
00:21:16,270 --> 00:21:18,250
she wanted to give me.

418
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:21,030
There are so many people
who live their entire lives

419
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:24,240
searching for the love
I had and threw away.

420
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:25,260
Love is priceless

421
00:21:25,260 --> 00:21:28,090
and we should all recognize
its tremendous power.

422
00:21:28,090 --> 00:21:31,020
♪

423
00:21:31,020 --> 00:21:34,060
I thought my story might prove
of special interest to you.

424
00:21:34,060 --> 00:21:36,190
So keep loving the people
you have around you.

425
00:21:36,190 --> 00:21:38,160
You're lucky to have them.

426
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:54,130
♪

427
00:21:54,130 --> 00:21:56,150
I'm so glad all of you
came back safe and sound.

428
00:21:56,150 --> 00:22:00,280
♪

429
00:22:00,280 --> 00:22:02,000
Did you catch fish?

430
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:03,150
What happened?

431
00:22:03,150 --> 00:22:05,030
Sorry, but no fish.

432
00:22:05,030 --> 00:22:07,060
Well, I hope you
all had a good time.

433
00:22:07,060 --> 00:22:08,210
Well, we did meet
an old fisherman

434
00:22:08,210 --> 00:22:10,170
and he told
a great story to us.

435
00:22:10,170 --> 00:22:12,200
Well, you'll be happy
to hear that Dr. Gensai

436
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:15,040
brought enough vegetables
and noodles for a feast.

437
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:16,090
It's almost ready.

438
00:22:16,090 --> 00:22:17,130
You girls get
your hands washed.

439
00:22:17,130 --> 00:22:18,270
I mean, you two are
hungry, aren't you?

440
00:22:18,270 --> 00:22:20,120
-Sure, let's eat!
-I'm starving!

441
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:23,050
(laughing)

442
00:22:23,050 --> 00:22:27,210
♪

443
00:22:27,210 --> 00:22:30,260
From now on, I will
cherish Kori's love

444
00:22:30,260 --> 00:22:33,220
like the precious
flower it is.

445
00:22:33,220 --> 00:22:45,210
♪

446
00:22:48,280 --> 00:23:12,270
♪

447
00:23:12,270 --> 00:23:15,170
(singing in foreign language)

448
00:23:15,170 --> 00:25:10,120
♪

